This diagram shows the high level steps in the value chain. Steps will align to Products that will be delivered by Prodict Teams.
The diagram servces as a way to put boundaries around the steps so that they are well defined. The steps are also hierachical.
We shodul use this diagrma to arrive at a common understandign of what we want to build/deliver. If something is missing or wrong, we should change it and produce another version.
Draft Screening Value Stream for Team Discussion

This tower provides the means to allocate participants to slots (for appointment based programmes) and equivalent in other programmes. It provides the control capabilities for national/local app't mgmt. It provides the control capabilities for multi-channel 2-way mgmt of participant interaction.
This tower manages the Next Best action after SEMs and will facilitate the future action for the participant. Addditionally, referral and outcome mgmt.

This tower gathers the full cohort for each screening programme (the Demand) and manages the subsequent Supply side capacity. For Release 0 this tower will allocate participants to Service Providers in advance of slot alloctation.

This tower is mainly about forward planning at the Screening Committee level. What are the new modalities ? Have they been proven? What are the dimensions of a future screening programme? This tower also provides the means to engage with UK citizens with screening. This is marketing, promotion etc ahead, during and after citizens have engaged with screening.

This tower manages the Screenign Event by modality and programme (ie there are multiple SEMs for Breast Screening: Mammography, Biopsy, Ultrasound). The tower starts at arrive at a screening location (a BSO (for breast), or bathroom (for bowel). It encompases logistics of moving test samples (electronically or physically) to a examination capability or lab. It ends when that modality assessment has been completed and has a formal observation.

Capacity Models: > Free Capacity - Based on unlimited capacity per location - with cohort allocted using defined rules - in order to assess an ideal allocation. > Planned Capacity - A Service Provider will have a planned capacity that it expects to be able to provide (this will be based on historic capacity, commissioned capacity and/or Free capacity. > Actual Capacity - This is capcity that the SErvice Provider has promised to provide.
